111
[div class=p 
	"Hello, and welcome to TASVideos! This page describes the rules and guidelines that 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=submissions|href=/Subs-List)
	" are judged by. (Intended for TAS authors; judges should see 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=here|href=/JudgeGuidelines)
	".)
	$LF
	"These guidelines can and will change or become more clarified as the site continues to grow, particularly if and when we receive submissions that challenge them. To learn the latest changes, read the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Movie Rules History|href=/MovieRules/History)
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"An important thing to keep in mind is that most submissions 
	[b 
		[em 
			"will
		]em
	]b
	" meet all of our requirements by default. This page is not meant to strictly list every rule that every submission must follow, it is meant to be used as a reference for users and staff to solve difficult situations and edge cases. We do not require or expect users to fully read and memorize this page before making submissions.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you have any questions that this page does not answer, or if you are unsure about the presence or absence of a rule, 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=ask a Judge on the forums|href=/Forum/Topics/19741)
	" or reach out to us on 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=our Discord server|href=/DiscordServer)
	". If you would like to suggest possible changes and updates to these rules, 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=use this thread|href=/Forum/Topics/22887)
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For more specific information on our accepted emulators and movie formats, see our 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Emulator Resources page|href=/EmulatorResources)
	".
	$LF
]div
